    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tools consisting of a long drill bit which pierces a spool-shaped object; used in conjunction with a bow to drill holes in brass, iron, and steel. Most often used by clock- and watchmakers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
